Description: Modern connection manager for Linux (SSH, RDP, VNC, SPICE, Zero Trust)
 RustConn is a modern connection manager for Linux desktops.
 It provides a GTK4-based GUI for managing SSH, RDP, VNC, SPICE,
 and Zero Trust remote connections with features like connection groups,
 credential management via KeePassXC and libsecret, session logging,
 connection history and statistics, and import/export from Asbru-CM,
 Remmina, SSH config, and Ansible inventory.
